name: Apple
description: A common, round fruit produced by the tree Malus domestica, cultivated in temperate climates.

name: Apricot
description: A round sweet and juicy stone fruit, resembling peach or plum in taste, with a yellow-orange flesh, lightly fuzzy skin and a large seed inside.

name: Avocado
description: The large, usually yellowish-green or black, pulpy fruit of the avocado tree.

name: Banana
description: An elongated curved tropical fruit that grows in bunches and has a creamy flesh and a smooth skin.

name: Bilberry
description: Vaccinium myrtillus, the wild European blueberry of the cowberry family.

name: Blackberry
description: A fruit-bearing shrub of the species Rubus fruticosus and some hybrids.

name: Blackcurrant
description: A shrub, Ribes nigrum, that produces small, very dark purple, edible berries.

name: Blueberry
description: An edible round berry, belonging to the cowberry group (Vaccinium sect. Cyanococcus), with flared crowns at the end, that turns blue on ripening.

name: Cantaloupe
description: A melon of species Cucumis melo subsp. melo with sweet orange flesh, with numerous cultivars in several cultivar groups.

name: Currant
description: A small dried grape, usually the Black Corinth grape, rarely more than 4mm diameter when dried.

name: Cherry
description: A small fruit, usually red, black or yellow, with a smooth hard seed and a short hard stem.

name: Clementine
description: A type of small, sweet orange, the result of a cross between a tangerine and Seville orange.

name: Damson
description: A subspecies of plum tree, Prunus domestica subsp. insititia, native to Eurasia.

name: Eggplant
description: The plant Solanum melongena.

name: Elderberry
description: The elder; a shrub or tree of the genus Sambucus.

name: Feijoa
description: A South American evergreen shrub, Acca sellowiana (syn. Feijoa sellowiana).

name: Gooseberry
description: A fruit, Ribes uva-crispa, related to the currant.

name: Grape
description: A small, round, smooth-skinned edible fruit, usually purple, red, or green, that grows in bunches on vines of genus Vitis.

name: Grapefruit
description: The tree of the species Citrus paradisi, a hybrid of pomelo (Citrus maxima) and sweet orange.

name: Guava
description: A tropical tree or shrub of the myrtle family, Psidium guajava.

name: Jackfruit
description: A tree, Artocarpus heterophyllus, of the Moraceae family, which produces edible fruit.

name: Kumquat
description: A small, orange citrus-like fruit which is native to Asia (Citrus japonica, syn. Fortunella japonica).

name: Legume
description: The fruit or seed of leguminous plants (as peas or beans) used for food.

name: Lemon
description: A yellowish citrus fruit.

name: Lychee
description: The Chinese tropical fruit tree Litchi chinensis, of the soapberry family.

name: Mango
description: A tropical Asian fruit tree, Mangifera indica.

name: Nectarine
description: A cultivar of the peach distinguished by its skin being smooth, not fuzzy.

name: Orange
description: An evergreen tree of the genus Citrus such as Citrus sinensis.

name: Peach
description: A particular rock found in tin mines, sometimes associated with chlorite.

name: Pear
description: An edible fruit produced by the pear tree, similar to an apple but elongated towards the stem.

name: Pomegranate
description: A fruit-bearing shrub or small tree, Punica granatum.

name: Raisin
description: A dried grape.

name: Rambutan
description: A tree, Nephelium lappaceum, of Southeast Asia.

name: Redcurrant
description: A deciduous shrub, Ribes rubrum, native to western Europe; any of certain cultivars of the shrub.

name: Satsuma
description: A seedless and easy-peeling cultivar of mandarin orange of Japanese origin; Citrus unshiu.

name: Strawberry
description: The sweet, usually red, edible fruit of certain plants of the genus Fragaria.

name: Tangerine
description: Any of several varieties of mandarin oranges.

name: Tomato
description: A widely cultivated plant, Solanum lycopersicum, having edible fruit.

name: Watermelon
description: A plant of the species Citrullus lanatus, bearing a melon-like fruit.
